HEADWORD: Erythrozyme
<hw>E*ryth"ro*zyme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'eryqro`s</grk> red + <?/ leaven.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A ferment extracted from madder root, possessing the
power of inducing alcoholic fermentation in solutions of
